      • move

        public Location move(int dx,
                     int dy,
                     int dz)
              throws model.exceptions.EntityIsDeadException,
                     model.exceptions.BadLocationException
        If (x,y,z) is the player’s current location, it ‘moves’ the player to location (x+dx,y+dy,z+dz).
        Parameters:
        dx - integer from range [-1,1] to change position in x-axis
        dy - integer from range [-1,1] to change position in y-axis
        dz - integer from range [-1,1] to change position in z-axis
        Returns:
        new location
        Throws:
        model.exceptions.EntityIsDeadException - if the player to be moved is dead
        model.exceptions.BadLocationException - if the target location is not adjacent to the current one, is occupied or is not valid

      • useItemInHand
